Composition

Question:- When you put two classes together like this youâ€™re using composition. Instead of inheriting their behavior, the ducks get their behavior by being composed with 
the right behavior object. 

Answer:- 
ğŸ“¦ What is Composition? Composition means putting one object inside another to use its behavior.

ğŸ” Inheritance vs Composition
            Concept	            Example	                            Meaning
            Inheritance	      class Duck extends FlyWithWings	Duck is a FlyWithWings (not ideal)
            Composition	      class Duck { FlyBehavior fly; }	Duck has a FlyBehavior (preferred)

ğŸ§  Why Composition is Better Here
      You can swap behaviors at runtime.
      Itâ€™s more flexible and reusable.
      You avoid tightly coupling behavior to one class.

âœ… Final One-Line Summary
Instead of inheriting flying and quacking, the duck uses those behaviors by containing them as objectsâ€”thatâ€™s composition.

